<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-11-06T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-11-06T08:00:00-05:00" n="767" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d767">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">755.93/25: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-11-06T13:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">November 6,
                                        1926—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received November 6—10:12
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>77. My telegram number 66, September 7, 11 a.m. Foreign Office has today
                            notified the Chinese Government that the Belgian Government will submit
                            the question surrounding abrogation of the Sino-Belgian treaty to the
                            Court of International Justice at The Hague.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>